al economic issues: the growth and composition of undergraduate enrollments, the supply of faculty in the academic labor market, and the cost of operating colleges and universities. The study provides valuable insights for administrators and scholars of education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBusiness. 0aCollege attendance. 0aCollege costs. 0aCollege teachers. 0aEducation, Higher. 0aEducation. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh  aeconomics, higher education, university, college, public policy studies, industrial, labor relations, american culture, united states of america, usa, demographics, economy, enrollment, students, inefficiency, institutions, educators, undergraduates, faculty, academics, attendance, teachers, professors, costs, productivity.1 aClotfelter, Charles T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEhrenberg, Ronald G., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aEhrenberg, Ronald G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGetz, Malcolm, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGetz, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiegfried, John J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226110622423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226110622/original  a978-3-11-066785-1  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles